# Implementation Plan - Paperclip Setup

This plan outlines the steps to set up the Paperclip project, install all necessary dependencies, and provide a startup batch file.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
No major changes to the codebase are expected, but we will ensure the environment is ready for development.

### [NEW] Start Script
#### [NEW] [start_paperclip.bat](file:///C:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip2/start_paperclip.bat)
A batch file to automate the startup of the Paperclip services.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `pnpm -r typecheck` to ensure there are no type errors after installation.
- Run `pnpm test:run` (if applicable) to verify the core logic.

### Manual Verification
- Open the UI at `http://localhost:3100` and verify it loads correctly.
- Check the health endpoint at `http://localhost:3100/api/health`.
